{"title_page": "Onset of deconfinement", "text_new": "[[File:NA61-NA49_horn.png|thumb|300px|The ratio of mean multiplicities of positively charged [[kaon]]s and [[pion]]s as a function of collision energy in collisions of two [[lead]] [[atomic nucleus|nuclei]] and [[proton]]\u2013proton interactions]]\n\nThe '''onset of deconfinement''' refers to the beginning of the creation of [[color confinement|deconfined]] [[phase (matter)|states]] of [[strong interaction|strongly interacting]] [[QCD matter|matter]] produced in [[heavy ion|nucleus-nucleus]] collisions with increasing collision energy (a [[quark\u2013gluon plasma]]).\n\nThe onset of [[deconfinement]] was predicted by [[Marek Gazdzicki]] and [[Mark I. Gorenstein]] to be located in the low energy range of the [[Super Proton Synchrotron]] (SPS) at the [[CERN|European Organization for Nuclear Research]] (CERN).<ref name=smes>\n{{cite journal\n |author=M. Gazdzicki\n |author2=M.I. Gorenstein\n |date=1999\n |title=On the early stage of nucleus\u2013nucleus collisions\n |url=http://th-www.if.uj.edu.pl/acta/vol30/abs/v30p2705.htm\n |journal=[[Acta Physica Polonica B]]\n |volume=30 |pages=2705\n |doi=\n |arxiv=hep-ph/9803462\n|bibcode = 1999AcPPB..30.2705G\n }}</ref> These predictions have been confirmed by the [[NA49 experiment]] at the CERN SPS within the energy scan programme.<ref name=evidence>\n{{cite journal\n |author=C. Alt\n |author2=et al. ([[NA experiment|NA49 collaboration]])\n |date=2008\n |title=Pion and kaon production in central Pb+Pb collisions at 20''A'' and 30''A''&nbsp;GeV: Evidence for the onset of deconfinement\n |journal=[[Physical Review C]]\n |volume=77 |pages=024903\n |doi=10.1103/PhysRevC.77.024903\n |arxiv=0710.0118\n|bibcode = 2008PhRvC..77b4903A\n |issue=2 }}</ref> The most famous of these is the \"horn\"  in the ratio of mean multiplicities of positively charged [[kaon]]s and [[pion]]s observed in collisions of two [[lead]] [[atomic nucleus|nuclei]] at the low energies of the SPS. \n\n[[Strangeness production]] in relativistic heavy-ion collisions is used for the detection of the onset of deconfinement.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Becattini|first=F.|year=2012|title=Strangeness and onset of deconfinement|url=http://link.springer.com/10.1134/S106377881205002X|journal=Physics of Atomic Nuclei|language=en|volume=75|issue=5|pages=646\u2013649|doi=10.1134/S106377881205002X|issn=1063-7788|via=}}</ref> \n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n*[http://na49info.web.cern.ch/na49info/ Description of the NA49 experiment]\n\n[[Category:Quark matter]]\n", "text_old": "[[File:NA61-NA49_horn.png|thumb|300px|The ratio of mean multiplicities of positively charged [[kaon]]s and [[pion]]s as a function of collision energy in collisions of two [[lead]] [[atomic nucleus|nuclei]] and [[proton]]\u2013proton interactions]]\n\nThe '''onset of deconfinement''' refers to the beginning of the creation of [[color confinement|deconfined]] [[phase (matter)|states]] of [[strong interaction|strongly interacting]] [[QCD matter|matter]] produced in [[heavy ion|nucleus-nucleus]] collisions with increasing collision energy (a [[quark\u2013gluon plasma]]).\n\nThe onset of [[deconfinement]] was predicted by [[Marek Gazdzicki]] and [[Mark I. Gorenstein]] to be located in the low energy range of the [[Super Proton Synchrotron]] (SPS) at the [[CERN|European Organization for Nuclear Research]] (CERN).<ref name=smes>\n{{cite journal\n |author=M. Gazdzicki\n |author2=M.I. Gorenstein\n |date=1999\n |title=On the early stage of nucleus\u2013nucleus collisions\n |url=http://th-www.if.uj.edu.pl/acta/vol30/abs/v30p2705.htm\n |journal=[[Acta Physica Polonica B]]\n |volume=30 |pages=2705\n |doi=\n |arxiv=hep-ph/9803462\n|bibcode = 1999AcPPB..30.2705G\n }}</ref> These predictions have been confirmed by the [[NA49 experiment]] at the CERN SPS within the energy scan programme.<ref name=evidence>\n{{cite journal\n |author=C. Alt\n |author2=et al. ([[NA experiment|NA49 collaboration]])\n |date=2008\n |title=Pion and kaon production in central Pb+Pb collisions at 20''A'' and 30''A''&nbsp;GeV: Evidence for the onset of deconfinement\n |journal=[[Physical Review C]]\n |volume=77 |pages=024903\n |doi=10.1103/PhysRevC.77.024903\n |arxiv=0710.0118\n|bibcode = 2008PhRvC..77b4903A\n |issue=2 }}</ref> The most famous of these is the \"horn\"  in the ratio of mean multiplicities of positively charged [[kaon]]s and [[pion]]s observed in collisions of two [[lead]] [[atomic nucleus|nuclei]] at the low energies of the SPS. \n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n*[http://na49info.web.cern.ch/na49info/ Description of the NA49 experiment]\n\n[[Category:Quark matter]]\n", "name_user": "Bibliophilen", "label": "safe", "comment": "Added relation to strangeness production", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Onset_of_deconfinement"}
